title: High Newborn Immunization Rate
description: In 2023, 100% of newborns in the Bahamas were protected against tetanus, showcasing a robust healthcare system for infants.

title: Strong Female Youth Employment
description: The employment to population ratio for females aged 15-24 in the Bahamas was 81.172% in 2023, indicating strong female participation in the workforce.

title: High Youth Employment Rate
description: In 2023, the Bahamas had a youth employment to population ratio of 79.588%, reflecting a vibrant job market for young individuals.

title: Exceptional Female Labor Force Participation
description: The labor force participation rate for females aged 15+ was 98.651% in 2023, highlighting gender inclusivity in the workforce.

title: Balanced Gender Labor Force Participation
description: In 2023, the ratio of female to male labor force participation was 101.96%, indicating a balanced gender representation in the workforce.

title: High Tariff Rates on Manufactured Products
description: The Bahamas had a tariff rate of 33.23% on manufactured products in 2022, which could impact trade competitiveness.

title: Elevated Tariff Rates on All Products
description: In 2022, the Bahamas applied a tariff rate of 26.31% on all products, potentially affecting import costs.

title: High Share of Tariff Lines with Specific Rates on Primary Products
description: 25.97% of tariff lines on primary products had specific rates in 2022, indicating a complex tariff structure.

title: Minimal Carbon Emissions from Energy Fugitive Sources
description: In 2023, the Bahamas recorded a negligible 0.0001 Mt CO2e emissions from energy fugitive sources, showcasing its commitment to low carbon emissions.

title: Children Living with HIV
description: As of 2022, there were 100 children aged 0-14 living with HIV in the Bahamas, highlighting a significant public health challenge.
